column1: Who will win the 2020 Screen Actors Guild Award for Outstanding Performance by a Female Actor in a Television Movie or Limited Series?
column5: ['Patricia Arquette (The Act)', 'Toni Collette (Unbelievable)', 'Joey King (The Act)', 'Emily Watson (Chernobyl)', 'Michelle Williams (Fosse/Verdon)', 'A tie or other outcome']

column6: Chernobyl has been critically praised, has received much press attention, good buzz (plus, I've seen it and it is a powerful story). The other contenders simply have not received as much press, buzz and (arguably) viewership.
The Act is the favorite. If the two stars cancel out each other, Toni Collette could steal.
